Six people were killed during a mass shooting in Umlazi N section, Durban, on Monday afternoon. The shooting happened in an informal settlement, according to Brigadier Jay Naicker, KwaZulu-Natal police spokesperson. “It is alleged that at 1pm, a group of men aged between 22 and 25 years old, were seated in a house at an informal settlement in N Section, Umlazi, when they were attacked by approximately seven men who were armed with pistols,” he said. Naicker said six men were instantly killed at the scene. A further two injured men were found by police near the scene and transferred to a nearby hospital for treatment. Naicker said police detectives have launched a manhunt for the unknown shooters. Six cases of murder and two of attempted murder were opened at the Umlazi Police Station. “We are appealing to anyone who may have information that can assist in the investigation to contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111 or utilise the MYSAPS app,” said Naicker. In January, Police Minister Bheki Cele said there had been 229 multiple murder shootings which resulted in 531 fatalities in KZN over the past 10 months.